<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="329" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="12.[2022,2617,1593,2016]" pageId="12" pageNumber="329">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3807305314" pageId="12" pageNumber="329">“Pai-sa Hsian, Hainan Island.” Interpreted by D. R. Frost and colleagues in 1991 as “Baisha Xian, which is an administrative unit at 19°13’N, 109°26’E,” China.</materialsCitation>
